Krishna&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15255697" author="joshrosen" created="Sun, 24 Apr 2016 19:19:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s already logic for handling this in the JVM Spark SQL&apos;s analyzer, so we don&apos;t need to add any specific error-handling logic in PySpark. Instead, we need to make sure that we always pass the complete set of arguments to the JVM API so that we can rely on it to perform the validation for us.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
